# Jira Workflow

Invoke with: *"get my tickets"*, *"show sprint issues"*, *"update ticket"*, *"search jira"*, *"create a bug"*, *"file a bug"*

This workflow covers Jira MCP operations. For the full development workflow (ticket to PR), see `feature-development.mdc`.

---

## 1. MCP Provider Detection

Two MCP servers can interact with Jira. Detect which is available and use it:

| Provider | Server ID | How to Detect |
|----------|-----------|---------------|
| **Atlassian Plugin** | `plugin-atlassian-atlassian` | Tools named `getJiraIssue`, `createJiraIssue`, etc. Requires `cloudId`. |
| **Jira MCP** | (standalone Jira MCP) | Tools named `jira_get_issue`, `jira_create_issue`, etc. No `cloudId` needed. |

### Atlassian Plugin: Getting the `cloudId`

Most Atlassian Plugin tools require a `cloudId`. To obtain it:

1. **From a URL** — If the user provides a link like `https://issues.redhat.com/browse/CNV-12345`, pass the site hostname (`issues.redhat.com`) as `cloudId`.
2. **Fallback** — If that fails, call `getAccessibleAtlassianResources` (no parameters) to list available sites and their cloud IDs.

### Tool Name Mapping

| Operation | Jira MCP | Atlassian Plugin |
|-----------|----------|------------------|
| Search issues (JQL) | `jira_search` | `searchJiraIssuesUsingJql` |
| Get issue details | `jira_get_issue` | `getJiraIssue` |
| Create issue | `jira_create_issue` | `createJiraIssue` |
| Add comment | `jira_add_comment` | `addCommentToJiraIssue` |
| Transition status | `jira_transition_issue` | `transitionJiraIssue` |
| Log work | `jira_add_worklog` | `addWorklogToJiraIssue` |
| Update fields | `jira_update_issue` | `editJiraIssue` |
| Get sprint issues | `jira_get_sprint_issues` | `searchJiraIssuesUsingJql` (with sprint JQL) |
| Get transitions | — | `getTransitionsForJiraIssue` |
| Search (natural language) | — | `searchAtlassian` |

### Parameter Name Mapping

| Concept | Jira MCP param | Atlassian Plugin param |
|---------|----------------|------------------------|
| Issue key | `issue_key` | `issueIdOrKey` |
| Project | `project_key` | `projectKey` |
| Issue type | `issue_type` | `issueTypeName` |
| JQL query | `jql` | `jql` |
| Description | `description` | `description` |
| Extra fields | `additional_fields` | `additional_fields` |
| Content format | — | `contentFormat` (`"markdown"` or `"adf"`) |
| Response format | — | `responseContentFormat` (`"markdown"` or `"adf"`) |

> **Tip**: When using Atlassian Plugin, always pass `contentFormat: "markdown"` and `responseContentFormat: "markdown"` for readable results.

