## 7. MCP Tool Reference

### Jira MCP Tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `jira_search` | Find tickets with JQL |
| `jira_get_issue` | Get ticket details |
| `jira_create_issue` | Create new issues |
| `jira_add_comment` | Add comments |
| `jira_transition_issue` | Change status |
| `jira_add_worklog` | Log time |
| `jira_update_issue` | Update fields |
| `jira_get_sprint_issues` | Get sprint issues |

### Atlassian Plugin Tools (Jira)

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `searchJiraIssuesUsingJql` | Find tickets with JQL (requires `cloudId`, `jql`) |
| `getJiraIssue` | Get ticket details (requires `cloudId`, `issueIdOrKey`) |
| `createJiraIssue` | Create new issues (requires `cloudId`, `projectKey`, `issueTypeName`, `summary`) |
| `addCommentToJiraIssue` | Add comments (requires `cloudId`, `issueIdOrKey`, `commentBody`) |
| `transitionJiraIssue` | Change status (requires `cloudId`, `issueIdOrKey`, `transition.id`) |
| `addWorklogToJiraIssue` | Log time (requires `cloudId`, `issueIdOrKey`, `timeSpent`) |
| `editJiraIssue` | Update fields (requires `cloudId`, `issueIdOrKey`, `fields`) |
| `getTransitionsForJiraIssue` | List available transitions (requires `cloudId`, `issueIdOrKey`) |
| `searchAtlassian` | Natural-language search across Jira and Confluence |
| `atlassianUserInfo` | Get current authenticated user info |
| `getAccessibleAtlassianResources` | List accessible sites / get `cloudId` |

Tools are called automatically when you make requests. Just describe what you want in natural language.

---

## 8. Tips

- Be specific: "Show bugs assigned to me" vs "show issues"
- Use project codes: "CNV-12345" not just "12345"
- Check ticket comments before starting work
- Add comments when starting/finishing work
- Document blockers in ticket comments
- When using Atlassian Plugin, prefer `contentFormat: "markdown"` for readable descriptions
- When transitioning issues via Atlassian Plugin, always call `getTransitionsForJiraIssue` first to discover valid transition IDs
